<title>USA: Public Service says SEC okays merger.</title>
<headline>Public Service says SEC okays merger.</headline>
<dateline>DENVER, Colo. 1997-08-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Public Service Co of Colorado and  Southwestern Public Service Co said on Friday that the Securities  and Exchange Commission had approved their plan to merge into a holding  company called New Century Energies.</p>
<p>In a statement, the companies said the approval signaled &quot;the first  successful merger of more than 20 pending or withdrawn investor-owned  electric utility mergers or acquisitions recently announced in the  midst of major utility restructuring.&quot;</p>
<p>With the SEC approval, received August 1, the merger becomes effective,  the companies said.</p>
<p>The new company will begin trading on the New York Stock Exchange  on August 4 under the symbol NCE.N.</p>
